# Backend Folder Structure (Nitro)

- `server/api/` — HTTP endpoints (H3 handlers). Use method suffix: `.get.ts`, `.post.ts`, etc.
- `server/utils/` — Reusable server utilities (e.g., `mongo.ts`). Prefer small, focused modules.
- `server/middleware/` — H3 event middleware (auth, logging, rate limiting) if needed.
- `server/plugins/` — Nitro plugins (initialize services). Keep minimal.

Conventions:

- Only server code here (never import these from client code).
- Validate input (query/body) defensively.
- Access MongoDB via the shared util; avoid instantiating clients in handlers.
